targets.rawSql:
SELECT DATE_TRUNC('day', timestamp) as time,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN obj_val = 'completed' THEN 1 END) as "Jobs completed per day",
       COUNT(CASE WHEN obj_val = 'rejected' THEN 1 END) as "Jobs rejected per day"
FROM events 
WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp)
    AND (scope = 'update:job')
    AND (obj_name = 'status')
    AND (obj_val IN ('completed', 'rejected'))
GROUP BY time
ORDER BY time

SELECT DATE_TRUNC('day', timestamp) as time, user_name as user,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN obj_val IN ('completed', 'rejected') THEN 1 END) as "Done by"
FROM events 
WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp)
    AND (scope = 'update:job')
    AND (obj_name = 'status')
    AND (obj_val IN ('completed', 'rejected'))
GROUP BY time, user
ORDER BY time, user

SELECT DATE_TRUNC('hour', timestamp) as time,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN obj_val = 'completed' THEN 1 END) as "Jobs completed per hour",
       COUNT(CASE WHEN obj_val = 'rejected' THEN 1 END) as "Jobs rejected per hour"
FROM events 
WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp)
    AND (scope = 'update:job')
    AND (obj_name = 'status')
    AND (obj_val IN ('completed', 'rejected'))
GROUP BY time
ORDER BY time

SELECT DATE_TRUNC('hour', timestamp) as time, user_name as user,
       COUNT(CASE WHEN obj_val IN ('completed', 'rejected') THEN 1 END) as "Done by"
FROM events 
WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp)
    AND (scope = 'update:job')
    AND (obj_name = 'status')
    AND (obj_val IN ('completed', 'rejected'))
GROUP BY time, user
ORDER BY time, user

WITH user_activity AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT DATE_TRUNC('hour', timestamp) AS time,
           toString(user_name) AS user
    FROM events
    WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp)
    ),
user_jobs AS (
    SELECT DATE_TRUNC('hour', timestamp) AS time,
           user_name AS user,
           COUNT(CASE WHEN obj_val IN ('completed', 'rejected') THEN 1 END) AS done_by
    FROM events 
    WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp)
        AND (scope = 'update:job')
        AND (obj_name = 'status')
        AND (obj_val IN ('completed', 'rejected'))
        GROUP BY time, user
)
SELECT DATE_TRUNC('day', ua.time) as time,
       COALESCE(SUM(uj.done_by) / COUNT(ua.time), 0) AS "Average jobs completed per hour"
FROM user_activity ua
LEFT JOIN user_jobs uj ON ua.time = uj.time AND ua.user = uj.user
GROUP BY time
ORDER BY time;

targets.rawSql:
WITH user_activity AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT DATE_TRUNC('hour', timestamp) AS time,
           toString(user_name) AS user
    FROM events
    WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp)
    ),
user_jobs AS (
    SELECT DATE_TRUNC('hour', timestamp) AS time,
           user_name AS user,
           COUNT(CASE WHEN obj_val IN ('completed', 'rejected') THEN 1 END) AS done_by
    FROM events 
    WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp)
        AND (scope = 'update:job')
        AND (obj_name = 'status')
        AND (obj_val IN ('completed', 'rejected'))
        GROUP BY time, user
)
SELECT DATE_TRUNC('day', ua.time) as time,
       ua.user,
       COALESCE(uj.done_by / COUNT(ua.time), 0) AS "Average jobs completed per active hour by"
FROM user_activity ua
LEFT JOIN user_jobs uj ON ua.time = uj.time AND ua.user = uj.user
GROUP BY time, ua.user, uj.done_by
ORDER BY time, ua.user;

panels.description: Overall time from job opening to job completion

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
     DATE_TRUNC('day', e2.timestamp) as time,
    AVG(TIMESTAMPDIFF(MINUTE, e1.timestamp, e2.timestamp)) AS "Overall average minutes to complete a job"
FROM events e1
LEFT JOIN events e2 ON e1.job_id = e2.job_id
WHERE
    $__timeFilter(e1.timestamp) AND e1.scope = 'load:job'
    AND (($__timeFilter(e2.timestamp) AND e2.scope = 'update:job' AND (e2.obj_val = 'completed' OR e2.obj_val = 'rejected')))
    AND e1.timestamp < e2.timestamp
    AND e1.user_name = e2.user_name
GROUP BY time
ORDER BY time

panels.description: Minutes  from job opening to job completion

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
     DATE_TRUNC('day', e2.timestamp) as time,
    e2.user_name AS user,
    AVG(TIMESTAMPDIFF(MINUTE, e1.timestamp, e2.timestamp)) AS "Avg minutes from opening to completing job by"
FROM events e1
LEFT JOIN events e2 ON e1.job_id = e2.job_id
WHERE
    $__timeFilter(e1.timestamp) AND e1.scope = 'load:job'
    AND (($__timeFilter(e2.timestamp) AND e2.scope = 'update:job' AND (e2.obj_val = 'completed' OR e2.obj_val = 'rejected')))
    AND e1.timestamp < e2.timestamp
    AND e1.user_name = e2.user_name
ORDER BY time, user

targets.rawSql:
WITH time_per_job AS (
    SELECT
        user_name as user,
        job_id as job,
        sum(JSONExtractUInt(payload, 'working_time')) / 1000 as time_per_job
    FROM events
    WHERE JSONHas(payload, 'working_time')
      AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
        AND source = 'client'
    GROUP BY user_name, job_id
),
     completed_jobs AS (
         SELECT DATE_TRUNC('day', timestamp) AS time,
                user_name AS user,
                job_id as job,
                COUNT(CASE WHEN obj_val IN ('completed', 'rejected') THEN 1 END) AS done_by
         FROM events
         WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp)
           AND (scope = 'update:job')
           AND (obj_name = 'status')
           AND (obj_val IN ('completed', 'rejected'))
                GROUP BY time, user, job_id
     )
SELECT DATE_TRUNC('day', completed.time) as time,
       AVG(job_time.time_per_job) AS "Average seconds to complete job"
FROM completed_jobs AS completed
         LEFT JOIN time_per_job AS job_time ON completed.job = job_time.job AND completed.user = job_time.user
GROUP BY time
ORDER BY time;

panels.title: Avg time [s] to complete a job per working time

targets.rawSql:
WITH time_per_job AS (
    SELECT
        user_name as user,
        job_id as job,
        sum(JSONExtractUInt(payload, 'working_time')) / 1000 as time_per_job
    FROM events
    WHERE JSONHas(payload, 'working_time')
      AND $__timeFilter(timestamp)
      AND user_name IN (${users})
      AND source = 'client'
    GROUP BY user_name, job_id
),
completed_jobs AS (
    SELECT DATE_TRUNC('day', timestamp) AS time,
           user_name AS user,
           job_id as job,
           COUNT(CASE WHEN obj_val IN ('completed', 'rejected') THEN 1 END) AS done_by
    FROM events
    WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp)
        AND (scope = 'update:job')
        AND (obj_name = 'status')
        AND (obj_val IN ('completed', 'rejected'))
GROUP BY time, user, job_id
)
SELECT DATE_TRUNC('day', completed.time) as time,
       completed.user as user,
       AVG(job_time.time_per_job) AS "Average seconds to complete job by"
FROM completed_jobs AS completed
         LEFT JOIN time_per_job AS job_time ON completed.job = job_time.job AND completed.user = job_time.user
GROUP BY time, completed.user
ORDER BY time, completed.user;
